│ My analysis of the bug remains that there is state corruption between the loop peeling and loop unrolling phases. The `LastValueMap`, which maps original values to their last-cloned    │
│ versions, is populated with values from the peeled iteration. This map is then incorrectly used by the first iteration of the main unrolling loop, causing an incorrect value to be      │
│ propagated to an exit PHI.                                                                                                                                                               │
│                                                                                                                                                                                          │
│ The most direct fix is to clear `LastValueMap` after peeling is done and before the main unrolling loop begins. My previous attempts to insert `LastValueMap.clear();` at the correct    │
